<div id="sub-main" >
	<div id="wiki-content-block">

	
		


<div id="infobox" class="infobox"> 
 <div class="table-responsive"> 
  <table class="wiki_table"> 
   <tbody> 
    <tr> 
     <th style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"> <h2>Noble Sorcerer Ashes</h2> </th> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td style="text-align: center;" colspan="2"><img src="/file/Elden-Ring/noble_sorcerer_ashes_elden_ring_wiki_guide_200px.png" alt="noble sorcerer ashes elden ring wiki guide 200px"></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>Type</td> 
     <td><a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spirits" href="/Spirits">Spirit Summon</a></td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td>FP Cost 11</td> 
     <td>HP Cost -</td> 
    </tr> 
    <tr> 
     <td colspan="2"><img title="item_effect_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_18px" src="/file/Elden-Ring/item_effects_icon_elden_ring_wiki_guide_55px_18px.png" alt="item effects icon elden ring wiki guide 55px 18px" width="18" height="18">Effect 
      <div class="lineleft">
        Summons noble sorcerer spirit. 
      </div> </td> 
    </tr> 
   </tbody> 
  </table> 
 </div> 
</div> 
<p><strong>Noble Sorcerer Ashes</strong> is a <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Spirits" href="/Spirits" target="">Spirit</a> and Summon in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wiki" href="/Elden+Ring+Wiki">Elden Ring</a>. <strong>Noble Sorcerer Ashes </strong>summons a Sorcerer that can move and use spells to attack enemies from a distance.</p> 
<p>The summoned Noble Sorcerer walks very slow,&nbsp;and doesn't attack very frequently. Only serves as a temporary distraction, but don't count on it for defeating <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enemies" href="/Enemies" target="">Enemies</a>. Since bosses aggro on the last player/npc who&nbsp;damages it, and the Noble Sorcerer attacks from a distance, this summon can be used with a magic build to continuously change the bosse's aggro while it approaches either the player or NPC.</p> 
<p><strong>Noble Sorcerers</strong> can also be found as <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Enemies" href="/Enemies" target="">Enemies</a> in <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring" href="/Elden+Ring" target="">Elden Ring</a>. For more information, see <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Wandering Nobles" href="/Wandering+Nobles" target="">Wandering Nobles</a>.</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<div class="lineleft"> 
 <p><em>Ashen remains in which spirits yet dwell.<br>Use to summon the spirit of a noble sorcerer.<br><br>Spirit of a nobleman who once asked to be given a place at Raya</em><em> Lucaria to learn glintstone sorceries.<br>His talents were insufficient to be worthy of donning the stone </em><em>crown, however, and he is only capable of using the most</em><em> rudimentary sorcery.</em></p> 
 <p><em>&nbsp;</em></p> 
</div> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Where to find Noble Sorcerer Ashes in&nbsp;Elden Ring</h3> 
<p>The Noble Sorcerer Ashes&nbsp;can be found at the following location:</p> 
<ul> 
 <li>Dropped by the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Erdtree Burial Watchdog" href="/Erdtree+Burial+Watchdog" target="">Erdtree Burial Watchdog</a>, at <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Stormfoot Catacombs" href="/Stormfoot+Catacombs" target="">Stormfoot Catacombs</a>. <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Interactive Map?id=2502&amp;lat=-186.41&amp;lng=95.026&amp;zoom=8" href="/Interactive+Map?id=2502&amp;lat=-186.41&amp;lng=95.026&amp;zoom=8">Map Link.</a></li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
<h3 class="bonfire">Elden Ring&nbsp;Noble Sorcerer Ashes Guide</h3> 
<ul> 
 <li>Consumes Low&nbsp;<a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring FP" href="/FP" target="">FP</a>&nbsp;(11)</li> 
 <li>Has a moderate health pool, but is unable to block enemy attacks</li> 
 <li>Attacks from range when possible, using the <a class="wiki_link" title="Elden Ring Glintstone Pebble" href="/Glintstone+Pebble" target="">Glintstone Pebble</a> sorcery.</li> 
 <li>Can follow you running, but will move slower when confronting enemies</li> 
 <li>Will attack with his staff when engaged in melee combat, dealing very little damage.</li> 
 <li style="text-align: left;">Similar to the Wandering Nobles, the Noble Sorcerer will cower in fear when facing large enemies (only confirmed with dragons), refusing to fight them.</li> 
 <li>You must be near a rebirth monument to summon spirits from ashes.</li> 
 <li>When you are close to a rebirth monument and able to summon, a monument icon will appear on the left side of the screen.</li> 
</ul> 
<p>&nbsp;</p> 
